    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I disabled the behaviour for planes now.\n\nBTW, another change which will probably be controversial is that if you order a unit to attack a target that has been revealed by another of your units (say, half-way across the map), then the first unit will abort the attack if the target should ever get under the fog again (for example because your other unit was killed).\n"
